The real trick to make an ending sing is to come back to the beginning \'97 the look of the beginning, the music of the beginning, the same lease or flake of ash or severed human head falling gently from the evening sky. Because then you can say in effect: 
\i Nothing has changed. All of this you\'92ve seen could come around again the same again. People don\'92t change. The world does not change. The color of blood in a dirty river has been the color of blood in dirty rivers since there was blood, dirt, rivers, and human eyes to see them.
\i0 \
